  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1035&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Limited Liability`
  line `Partnership Act, 2008.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 . 31st March, 2009, vide notification No. S.O. 891 (E), dated 31st March, 2009, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `Sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (1036)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1036&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "address", in relation to a partner of a limited liability partnership, means--`
  line
  line `(i) if an individual, his usual residential address; and`
  line
  line `(ii) if a body corporate, the address of its registered office;`
  line
  line `(b) "advocate" means an advocate as defined in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the`
  line `Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(c) "Appellate Tribunal" means the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal constituted under`
  line `^1[section 410] of ^2[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)];;`
  line
  line `(d) "body corporate" means a company as defined in ^3[clause (20) of section 2] of ^2[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a limited liability partnership registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) a limited liability partnership incorporated outside India; and`
  line
  line `(iii) a company incorporated outside India,`
  line
  line `but does not include--`
  line
  line `(i) a corporation sole;`
  line
  line `(ii) a co-operative society registered under any law for the time being in force; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any other body corporate (not being a company as defined in ^3[clause (20) of section 2] of ^2[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] or a limited liability partnership as defined in this`
  line `Act), which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line behalf;;
  line
  line `(e) "business" includes every trade, profession, service 5`
  line `^4[and occupation except any activity`
  line `which the Central Government may, by notification, exclude];`
  line
  line `(f) "chartered accountant" means a chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) and who has obtained a certificate`
  line `of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(g) company secretary means a company secretary as defined in clause (c) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980) and who has obtained a certificate of`
  line `practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "cost accountant" means a cost accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959) and who has obtained a`
  line `certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "Court", with respect to any offence under this Act, means the Court having jurisdiction as per`
  line `the provisions of section 77;`
  line
  line `(j) "designated partner" means any partner designated as such pursuant to section 7;`
  line
  line `(k) ''entity" means any body corporate and includes, for the purposes of sections 18, 46, 47, 48,`
  line `49, 50, 52 and 53, a firm setup under the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932);`
  line
  line `(l) "financial year", in relation to a limited liability partnership, means the period from the 1st day`
  line `of April of a year to the 31st day of March of the following year:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a limited liability partnership incorporated after the 30th day of`
  line `September of a year, the financial year may end on the 31st day of March of the year next following`
  line `that year;`
  line
  line `(m) "foreign limited liability partnership" means a limited liability partnership formed,`
  line `incorporated or registered outside India which establishes a place of business within India;`
  line
  line `(n) "limited liability partnership" means a partnership formed and registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "limited liability partnership" agreement means any written agreement between the partners of`
  line `the limited liability partnership or between the limited liability partnership and its partners which`
  line `determines the mutual rights and duties of the partners and their rights and duties in relation to that`
  line `limited liability partnership;`
  line
  line `(p) "name", in relation to a partner of a limited liability partnership, means--`
  line
  line `(i) if an individual, his forename, middle name and surname; and`
  line
  line `(ii) if a body corporate, its registered name;`
  line
  line `(q) "partner", in relation to a limited liability partnership, means any person who becomes a`
  line `partner in the limited liability partnership in accordance with the limited liability partnership`
  line agreement;
  line
  line `(r) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^5[(ra) "Regional Director" means a person appointed as such by Central Government for the`
  line `purpose of this Act or the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `^6[(s) "Registrar" means a person appointed by the Central Government as Registrar, an Additional`
  line `Registrar, a Joint Registrar, a Deputy Registrar or an Assistant Registrar, for the purpose of this Act`
  line `or the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)];`
  line
  line `(t) "Schedule'' means a Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `^5[(ta) "small limited liability" partnership means a limited liability partnership--`
  line
  line `(i) the contribution of which, does not exceed twenty-five lakh rupees or such higher amount,`
  line `not exceeding five crore rupees, as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the turnover of which, as per the Statement of Accounts and Solvency for the immediately`
  line `preceding financial year, does not exceed forty lakh rupees or such higher amount, not exceeding`
  line `fifty crore rupees, as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(iii) which meets such other requirements as may be prescribed,`
  line
  line `and fulfils such terms and conditions as may be prescribed;]`
  line
  line `(u) "Tribunal "means the National Company Law Tribunal constituted under ^6[section 408] of ^2[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)].`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in ^2[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 3, for "sub-section (1) of section 10FR" (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)" (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "section 3" (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "and occupation" (w.e.f. 1-4-2022)`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 3, for clause (s) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 3, for clause (s) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 3 "sub-section (1) of section 10FB" (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (1037)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Limited liability partnership to be body corporate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1037&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) A limited liability partnership is a body`
  line `corporate formed and incorporated under this Act and is a legal entity separate from that of its partners.`
  line
  line `(2) A limited liability partnership shall have perpetual succession.`
  line
  line `(3) Any change in the partners of a limited liability partnership shall not affect the existence, rights or`
  line `liabilities of the limited liability partnership.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (1038)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Non-applicability of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1038&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided, the`
  line `provisions of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932) shall not apply to a limited liability`
  line partnership.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (1039)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Partners.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1039&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any individual or body corporate may be a partner in a limited liability partnership:`
  line
  line `Provided that an individual shall not be capable of becoming a partner of a limited liability`
  line `partnership, if--`
  line
  line `(a) he has been found to be of unsound mind by a Court of competent jurisdiction and the finding`
  line `is in force;`
  line
  line `(b) he is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) he has applied to be adjudicated as an insolvent and his application is pending.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (1040)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Minimum number of partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1040&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every limited liability partnership shall have at least two`
  line partners.
  line
  line `(2) If at any time the number of partners of a limited liability partnership is reduced below two and`
  line `the limited liability partnership carries on business for more than six months while the number is so`
  line `reduced, the person, who is the only partner of the limited liability partnership during the time that it so`
  line `carries on business after those six months and has the knowledge of the fact that it is carrying on business`
  line `with him alone, shall be liable personally for the obligations of the limited liability partnership incurred`
  line `during that period.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1041)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Designated partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1041&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every limited liability partnership shall have at least two designated`
  line `partners who are individuals and at least one of them shall be a resident in India:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of a limited liability partnership in which all the partners are bodies corporate or`
  line `in which one or more partners are individuals and bodies corporate, at least two individuals who are`
  line `partners of such limited liability partnership or nominees of such bodies corporate shall act as designated`
  line partners.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the term resident in India means a person who has`
  line `stayed in India for a period of not less than one hundred and ^1[twenty days during the financial year].`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(i) if the incorporation document--`
  line
  line `(a) specifies who are to be designated partners, such persons shall be designated partners on`
  line `incorporation; or`
  line
  line `(b) states that each of the partners from time to time of limited liability partnership is to be`
  line `designated partner, every such partner shall be a designated partner;`
  line
  line `(ii) any partner may become a designated partner by and in accordance with the limited liability`
  line `partnership agreement and a partner may cease to be a designated partner in accordance with limited`
  line `liability partnership agreement.`
  line
  line `(3) An individual shall not become a designated partner in any limited liability partnership unless he`
  line `has given his prior consent to act as such to the limited liability partnership in such form and manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Every limited liability partnership shall file with the registrar the particulars of every individual`
  line `who has given his consent to act as designated partner in such form and manner as may be prescribed`
  line `within thirty days of his appointment.`
  line
  line `(5) An individual eligible to be a designated partner shall satisfy such conditions and requirements as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) Every designated partner of a limited liability partnership shall obtain a Designated Partner`
  line `Identification Number (DPIN) from the Central Government and the provisions of ^2[sections 153 to 159] (both inclusive) of ^3[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] shall apply mutatis mutandis for the said`
  line purpose.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 4, for “eighty-two days during the immediately preceding one year” (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “sections 266A to 266G” (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)” (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1042)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Liabilities of designated partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1042&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Unless expressly provided otherwise in this Act, a`
  line `designated partner shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) responsible for the doing of all acts, matters and things as are required to be done by the`
  line `limited liability partnership in respect of compliance of the provisions of this Act including filing of`
  line `any document, return, statement and the like report pursuant to the provisions of this Act and as may`
  line `be specified in the limited liability partnership agreement; and`
  line
  line `(b) liable to all penalties imposed on the limited liability partnership for any contravention of`
  line `those provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1043)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Changes in designated partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1043&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `A limited liability partnership may appoint a designated`
  line `partner within thirty days of a vacancy arising for any reason and provisions of sub-section (4) and`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 7 shall apply in respect of such new designated partner:`
  line
  line `Provided that if no designated partner is appointed, or if at any time there is only one designated`
  line `partner, each partner shall be deemed to be a designated partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1044)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Punishment for contravention of sections 7 and 9.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1044&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the limited liability partnership`
  line `contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 7, the limited liability partnership and its every`
  line `partner shall be ^1[liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees and in case of continuing contravention, with a further`
  line `penalty of one hundred rupees for each day after the first during which such contravention continues, subject to a`
  line `maximum of one lakh rupees for the limited liability partnership and fifty thousand rupees for every partner of such`
  line `limited liability partnership].`
  line
  line `^2[(2) If the limited liability partnership contravenes the provision of sub-section (4) of section 7, such`
  line `limited liability partnership and its every designated partner shall be liable to a penalty of five thousand`
  line `rupees and in case of continuing contravention, with a further penalty of one hundred rupees for each day`
  line `after the first during which such contravention continues, subject to a maximum of fifty thousand rupees`
  line `for the limited liability partnership and twenty-five thousand rupees for its every designated partner.`
  line
  line `(3) If the limited liability partnership contravenes the provisions of sub-section (5) of section 7 or`
  line `section 9, such limited liability partnership and its every partner shall be liable to a penalty of ten`
  line `thousand rupees, and in case of continuing contravention, with a further penalty of one hundred rupees for`
  line `each day after the first during which such contravention continues, subject to a maximum of one lakh`
  line `rupees for the limited liability partnership and fifty thousand rupees for its every partner.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for punishable with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees, but which may extend to five`
  line `lakh rupees (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 31of 2021, s. 5, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1045)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Incorporation document.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1045&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) For a limited liability partnership to be incorporated,--`
  line
  line `(a) two or more persons associated for carrying on a lawful business with a view to profit shall`
  line `subscribe their names to an incorporation document;`
  line
  line `(b) the incorporation document shall be filed in such manner and with such fees, as may be`
  line `prescribed with the Registrar of the State in which the registered office of the limited liability`
  line `partnership is to be situated; and`
  line
  line `(c) there shall be filed along with the incorporation document, a statement in the prescribed form,`
  line `made by either an advocate, or a Company Secretary or a Chartered Accountant or a Cost`
  line `Accountant, who is engaged in the formation of the limited liability partnership and by any one who`
  line `subscribed his name to the incorporation document, that all the requirements of this Act and the rules`
  line `made thereunder have been complied with, in respect of incorporation and matters precedent and`
  line `incidental thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) The incorporation document shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be in a form as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) state the name of the limited liability partnership;`
  line
  line `(c) state the proposed business of the limited liability partnership;`
  line
  line `(d) state the address of the registered office of the limited liability partnership;`
  line
  line `(e) state the name and address of each of the persons who are to be partners of the limited liability`
  line `partnership on incorporation;`
  line
  line `(f) state the name and address of the persons who are to be designated partners of the limited`
  line `liability partnership on incorporation;`
  line
  line `(g) contain such other information concerning the proposed limited liability partnership as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) If a person makes a statement under clause (c) of sub-section (1) which he--`
  line
  line `(a) knows to be false; or`
  line
  line `(b) does not believe to be true,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than ten thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1046)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Incorporation by registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1046&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the requirements imposed by clauses (b) and (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 11 have been complied with, the Registrar shall retain the incorporation`
  line `document and, unless the requirement imposed by clause (a) of that sub-section has not been complied`
  line `with, he shall, within a period of fourteen days--`
  line
  line `(a) register the incorporation document; and`
  line
  line `(b) give a certificate that the limited liability partnership is incorporated by the name specified`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar may accept the statement delivered under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 11`
  line `as sufficient evidence that the requirement imposed by clause (a) of that sub-section has been complied`
  line with.
  line
  line `(3) The certificate issued under clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall be signed by the Registrar and`
  line `authenticated by his official seal.`
  line
  line `(4) The certificate shall be conclusive evidence that the limited liability partnership is incorporated by`
  line `the name specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1047)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Registered office of limited liability partnership and change therein.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 6, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1047&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every limited`
  line `liability partnership shall have a registered office to which all communications and notices may be`
  line `addressed and where they shall be received.`
  line
  line `(2) A document may be served on a limited liability partnership or a partner or designated partner`
  line `thereof by sending it by post under a certificate of posting or by registered post or by any other manner, as`
  line `may be prescribed, at the registered office and any other address specifically declared by the limited`
  line `liability partnership for the purpose in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) A limited liability partnership may change the place of its registered office and file the notice of`
  line `such change with the Registrar in such form and manner and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed and any such change shall take effect only upon such filing.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) If any default is made in complying with the requirements of this section, the limited liability`
  line `partnership and its every partner shall be liable to a penalty of five hundred rupees for each day during`
  line `which the default continues, subject to a maximum of fifty thousand rupees for the limited liability`
  line `partnership and its every partner.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (1048)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Effect of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1048&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `On registration, a limited liability partnership shall, by its name, be`
  line `capable of--`
  line
  line `(a) suing and being sued;`
  line
  line `(b) acquiring, owning, holding and developing or disposing of property, whether movable or`
  line `immovable, tangible or intangible;`
  line
  line `(c) having a common seal, if it decides to have one; and`
  line
  line `(d) doing and suffering such other acts and things as bodies corporate may lawfully do and suffer.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (1049)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Name.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1049&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every limited liability partnership shall have either the words limited liability`
  line `partnership or the acronym LLP as the last words of its name.`
  line
  line `(2) No limited liability partnership shall be registered by a name which, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government is--`
  line
  line `(a) undesirable; or`
  line
  line `^1[(b) identical or too nearly resembles to that of any other limited liability partnership or a`
  line `company or a registered trade mark of any other person under the Trade Marks Act, 1999 (47 of`
  line `1999).]`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (1050)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Reservation of name.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1050&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person may apply in such form and manner and accompanied by`
  line `such fee as may be prescribed to the Registrar for the reservation of a name set out in the application as--`
  line
  line `(a) the name of a proposed limited liability partnership; or`
  line
  line `(b) the name to which a limited liability partnership proposes to change its name.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon receipt of an application under sub-section (1) and on payment of the prescribed fee, the`
  line `Registrar may, if he is satisfied, subject to the rules prescribed by the Central Government in the matter,`
  line `that the name to be reserved is not one which may be rejected on any ground referred to in sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 15, reserve the name for a period of three months from the date of intimation by the Registrar.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (1051)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Rectification of name of limited liability partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 8, for section 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1051&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sections 15 and 16, if through inadvertence or otherwise, a limited liability partnership, on its`
  line `first registration or on its registration by a new name, is registered by a name which is identical with or`
  line `too nearly resembles to--`
  line
  line `(a) that of any other limited liability partnership or a company; or`
  line
  line `(b) a registered trade mark of a proprietor under the Trade Marks Act, 1999 (47 of 1999),`
  line
  line `as is likely to be mistaken for it, then on an application of such limited liability partnership or`
  line `proprietor referred to in clauses (a) and (b) respectively or a company, the Central Government may`
  line `direct that such limited liability partnership to change its name or new name within a period of three`
  line `months from the date of issue of such direction:`
  line
  line `Provided that an application of the proprietor of the registered trade marks shall be maintainable`
  line `within a period of three years from the date of incorporation or registration or change of name of the`
  line `limited liability partnership under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a limited liability partnership changes its name or obtains a new name under`
  line `sub-section (1), it shall within a period of fifteen days from the date of such change, give notice of the`
  line `change to Registrar along with the order of the Central Government, who shall carry out necessary`
  line `changes in the certificate of incorporation and within thirty days of such change in the certificate of`
  line `incorporation, such limited liability partnership shall change its name in the limited liability partnership`
  line agreement.
  line
  line `(3) If the limited liability partnership is in default in complying with any direction given under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government shall allot a new name to the limited liability partnership in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed and the Registrar shall enter the new name in the register of limited liability`
  line `partnerships in place of the old name and issue a fresh certificate of incorporation with new name, which`
  line `the limited liability partnership shall use thereafter:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall prevent a limited liability partnership from`
  line `subsequently changing its name in accordance with the provisions of section 16.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (1052)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1052&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `18. [Application for direction to change name in certain circumstances]. Omitted by the Limited`
  line `liability Partnership(Amendment) Act, 2021 (31 of 2021), s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (1053)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Change of registered name.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1053&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any limited liability partnership may change its name registered`
  line `with the Registrar by filing with him a notice of such change in such form and manner and on payment of`
  line `such fees as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (1054)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Penalty for improper use of words "limited liability partnership" or "LLP".`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1054&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `If any person`
  line `or persons carry on business under any name or title of which the words "Limited Liability Partnership"`
  line `or "LLP" or any contraction or imitation thereof is or are the last word or words, that person or each of`
  line `those persons shall, unless duly incorporated as limited liability partnership, be punishable with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (1055)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Publication of name and limited liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 10, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1055&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every limited liability partnership shall ensure`
  line `that its invoices, official correspondence and publications bear the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the name, address of its registered office and registration number of the limited liability`
  line `partnership; and`
  line
  line `(b) a statement that it is registered with limited liability.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) If the limited liability partnership contravenes the provisions of this section, the limited liability`
  line `partnership shall be liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (1056)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Eligibility to be partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1056&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `On the incorporation of a limited liability partnership, the persons`
  line `who subscribed their names to the incorporation document shall be its partners and any other person may`
  line `become a partner of the limited liability partnership by and in accordance with the limited liability`
  line `partnership agreement.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (1057)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Relationship of partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1057&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided by this Act, the mutual rights and`
  line `duties of the partners of a limited liability partnership, and the mutual rights and duties of a limited`
  line `liability partnership and its partners, shall be governed by the limited liability partnership agreement`
  line `between the partners, or between the limited liability partnership and its partners.`
  line
  line `(2) The limited liability partnership agreement and any changes, if any, made therein shall be filed`
  line `with the Registrar in such form, manner and accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) An agreement in writing made before the incorporation of a limited liability partnership between`
  line `the persons who subscribe their names to the incorporation document may impose obligations on the`
  line `limited liability partnership, provided such agreement is ratified by all the partners after the incorporation`
  line `of the limited liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(4) In the absence of agreement as to any matter, the mutual rights and duties of the partners and the`
  line `mutual rights and duties of the limited liability partnership and the partners shall be determined by the`
  line `provisions relating to that matter as are set-out in the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (1058)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Cessation of partnership interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1058&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person may cease to be a partner of a limited liability`
  line `partnership in accordance with an agreement with the other partners or, in the absence of agreement with`
  line `the other partners as to cessation of being a partner, by giving a notice in writing of not less than thirty`
  line `days to the other partners of his intention to resign as partner.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall cease to be a partner of a limited liability partnership--`
  line
  line `(a) on his death or dissolution of the limited liability partnership; or`
  line
  line `(b) if he is declared to be of unsound mind by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(c) if he has applied to be adjudged as an insolvent or declared as an insolvent.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person has ceased to be a partner of a limited liability partnership (hereinafter referred to`
  line `as "former partner"), the former partner is to be regarded (in relation to any person dealing with the`
  line `limited liability partnership) as still being a partner of the limited liability partnership unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the person has notice that the former partner has ceased to be a partner of the limited liability`
  line `partnership; or`
  line
  line `(b) notice that the former partner has ceased to be a partner of the limited liability partnership has`
  line `been delivered to the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(4) The cessation of a partner from the limited liability partnership does not by itself discharge the`
  line `partner from any obligation to the limited liability partnership or to the other partners or to any other`
  line `person which he incurred while being a partner.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a partner of a limited liability partnership ceases to be a partner, unless otherwise provided`
  line `in the limited liability partnership agreement, the former partner or a person entitled to his share in`
  line `consequence of the death or insolvency of the former partner, shall be entitled to receive from the limited`
  line `liability partnership--`
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to the capital contribution of the former partner actually made to the limited`
  line `liability partnership; and`
  line
  line `(b) his right to share in the accumulated profits of the limited liability partnership, after the`
  line `deduction of accumulated losses of the limited liability partnership, determined as at the date the`
  line `former partner ceased to be a partner.`
  line
  line `(6) A former partner or a person entitled to his share in consequence of the death or insolvency of the`
  line `former partner shall not have any right to interfere in the management of the limited liability partnership.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (1059)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Registration of changes in partners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 11, for sub-sections (4) and (5) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1059&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every partner shall inform the limited liability`
  line `partnership of any change in his name or address within a period of fifteen days of such change.`
  line
  line `(2) A limited liability partnership shall--`
  line
  line `(a) where a person becomes or ceases to be a partner, file a notice with the Registrar within thirty`
  line `days from the date he becomes or ceases to be a partner; and`
  line
  line `(b) where there is any change in the name or address of a partner, file a notice with the Registrar`
  line `within thirty days of such change.`
  line
  line `(3) A notice filed with the Registrar under sub-section (2)--`
  line
  line `(a) shall be in such form and accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) shall be signed by the designated partner of the limited liability partnership and authenticated`
  line `in a manner as may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(c) if it relates to an incoming partner, shall contain a statement by such partner that he consents`
  line `to becoming a partner, signed by him and authenticated in the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) If the limited liability partnership contravenes the provisions of sub-section (2), the limited`
  line `liability partnership and its every designated partner shall be liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(5) If the contravention referred to in sub-section (1) is made by any partner of the limited liability`
  line `partnership, such partner shall be liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees.]`
  line
  line `(6) Any person who ceases to be a partner of a limited liability partnership may himself file with the`
  line `Registrar the notice referred to in sub-section (3) if he has reasonable cause to believe that the limited`
  line `liability partnership may not file the notice with the Registrar and in case of any such notice filed by a`
  line `partner, the Registrar shall obtain a confirmation to this effect from the limited liability partnership unless`
  line `the limited liability partnership has also filed such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that where no confirmation is given by the limited liability partnership within fifteen days,`
  line `the registrar shall register the notice made by a person ceasing to be a partner under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (1060)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Partner as agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1060&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every partner of a limited liability partnership is, for the purpose of the`
  line `business of the limited liability partnership, the agent of the limited liability partnership, but not of other`
  line partners.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (1061)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Extent of liability of limited liability partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1061&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) A limited liability partnership is not`
  line `bound by anything done by a partner in dealing with a person if--`
  line
  line `(a) the partner in fact has no authority to act for the limited liability partnership in doing a`
  line `particular act; and`
  line
  line `(b) the person knows that he has no authority or does not know or believe him to be a partner of`
  line `the limited liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(2) The limited liability partnership is liable if a partner of a limited liability partnership is liable to`
  line `any person as a result of a wrongful act or omission on his part in the course of the business of the limited`
  line `liability partnership or with its authority.`
  line
  line `(3) An obligation of the limited liability partnership whether arising in contract or otherwise, shall be`
  line `solely the obligation of the limited liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(4) The liabilities of the limited liability partnership shall be met out of the property of the limited`
  line `liability partnership.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (1062)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Extent of liability of partner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1062&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) A partner is not personally liable, directly or indirectly for an`
  line `obligation referred to in sub-section (3) of section 27 solely by reason of being a partner of the limited`
  line `liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (3) of section 27 and sub-section (1) of this section shall not affect`
  line `the personal liability of a partner for his own wrongful act or omission, but a partner shall not be`
  line `personally liable for the wrongful act or omission of any other partner of the limited liability partnership.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (1063)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Holding out.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=1063&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, who by words spoken or written or by conduct, represents`
  line `himself, or knowingly permits himself to be represented to be a partner in a limited liability partnership is`
  line `liable to any person who has on the faith of any such representation given credit to the limited liability`
  line `partnership, whether the person representing himself or represented to be a partner does or does not know`
  line `that the representation has reached the person so giving credit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any credit is received by the limited liability partnership as a result of such`
  line `representation, the limited liability partnership shall, without prejudice to the liability of the person so`
  line `representing himself or represented to be a partner, be liable to the extent of credit received by it or any`
  line `financial benefit derived thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) Where after a partner's death the business is continued in the same limited liability partnership`
  line `name, the continued use of that name or of the deceased partner's name as a part thereof shall not of itself`
  line `make his legal representative or his estate liable for any act of the limited liability partnership done after`
  line `his death.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (49001)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Unlimited liability in case of fraud.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 12, for “two years” (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49001&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of an act carried out by a limited liability`
  line `partnership, or any of its partners, with intent to defraud creditors of the limited liability partnership or`
  line `any other person, or for any fraudulent purpose, the liability of the limited liability partnership and`
  line `partners who acted with intent to defraud creditors or for any fraudulent purpose shall be unlimited for all`
  line `or any of the debts or other liabilities of the limited liability partnership:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case any such act is carried out by a partner, the limited liability partnership is liable`
  line `to the same extent as the partner unless it is established by the limited liability partnership that such act`
  line `was without the knowledge or the authority of the limited liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any business is carried on with such intent or for such purpose as mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1), every person who was knowingly a party to the carrying on of the business in the manner`
  line `aforesaid shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^1[five years] and with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a limited liability partnership or any partner or designated partner or employee of such`
  line `limited liability partnership has conducted the affairs of the limited liability partnership in a fraudulent`
  line `manner, then without prejudice to any criminal proceedings which may arise under any law for the time`
  line `being in force, the limited liability partnership and any such partner or designated partner or employee`
  line `shall be liable to pay compensation to any person who has suffered any loss or damage by reason of such`
  line `conduct:`
  line
  line `Provided that such limited liability partnership shall not be liable if any such partner or designated`
  line `partner or employee has acted fraudulently without knowledge of the limited liability partnership.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (49002)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Whistle blowing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49002&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court or Tribunal may reduce or waive any penalty leviable against`
  line `any partner or employee of a limited liability partnership, if it is satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) such partner or employee of a limited liability partnership has provided useful information`
  line `during investigation of such limited liability partnership; or`
  line
  line `(b) when any information given by any partner or employee (whether or not during investigation)`
  line `leads to limited liability partnership or any partner or employee of such limited liability partnership`
  line `being convicted under this Act or any other Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No partner or employee of any limited liability partnership may be discharged, demoted,`
  line `suspended, threatened, harassed or in any other manner discriminated against the terms and conditions of`
  line `his limited liability partnership or employment merely because of his providing information or causing`
  line `information to be provided pursuant to sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (49003)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Form of contribution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49003&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) A contribution of a partner may consist of tangible, movable or`
  line `immovable or intangible property or other benefit to the limited liability partnership, including money,`
  line `promissory notes, other agreements to contribute cash or property, and contracts for services performed or`
  line `to be performed.`
  line
  line `(2) The monetary value of contribution of each partner shall be accounted for and disclosed in the`
  line `accounts of the limited liability partnership in the manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (49004)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Obligation to contribute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49004&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The obligation of a partner to contribute money or other property`
  line `or other benefit or to perform services for a limited liability partnership shall be as per the limited liability`
  line `partnership agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) A creditor of a limited liability partnership, which extends credit or otherwise acts in reliance on`
  line `an obligation described in that agreement, without notice of any compromise between partners, may`
  line `enforce the original obligation against such partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (49005)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Maintenance of books of account, other records and audit, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 13, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49005&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The limited liability`
  line `partnership shall maintain such proper books of account as may be prescribed relating to its affairs for`
  line `each year of its existence on cash basis or accrual basis and according to double entry system of`
  line `accounting and shall maintain the same at its registered office for such period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every limited liability partnership shall, within a period of six months from the end of each`
  line `financial year, prepare a Statement of Account and Solvency for the said financial year as at the last day`
  line `of the said financial year in such form as may be prescribed, and such statement shall be signed by the`
  line `designated partners of the limited liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(3) Every limited liability partnership shall file within the prescribed time, the Statement of Account`
  line `and Solvency prepared pursuant to sub-section (2) with the Registrar every year in such form and manner`
  line `and accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of limited liability partnerships shall be audited in accordance with such rules as`
  line `may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt any class`
  line `or classes of limited liability partnerships from the requirements of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) Any limited liability partnership which fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (3),`
  line `such limited liability partnership and its designated partners shall be liable to a penalty of one hundred`
  line `rupees for each day during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees for the`
  line `limited liability partnership and fifty thousand rupees for every designated partner.`
  line
  line `(6) Any limited liability partnership which fails to comply with the provisions of sub-section (1),`
  line `sub-section (2) and sub-section (4), such limited liability partnership shall be punishable with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees, but may extend to five lakh rupees and every`
  line `designated partner of such limited liability partnership shall be punishable with fine which shall not be`
  line `less than ten thousand rupees, but may extend to one lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_a:
  sectionId (63905)
  sectionNo 34A
  orderNo 35
  title `Accounting and auditing standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 14, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=63905&sectionno=34A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_34_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[The Central Government may, in consultation with`
  line `the National Financial Reporting Authority constituted under section 132 of the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013),--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribe the standards of accounting; and`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the standards of auditing,`
  line
  line `as recommended by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949), for a class or classes of limited liability partnerships.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (49006)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Annual return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sub-sections (2) and (3) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49006&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every limited liability partnership shall file an annual return duly`
  line `authenticated with the Registrar within sixty days of closure of its financial year in such form and manner`
  line `and accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) If any limited liability partnership fails to file its annual return under sub-section (1) before the expiry of`
  line `the period specified therein, such limited liability partnership and its designated partners shall be liable to a penalty`
  line `of one hundred rupees for each day during which such failure continues, subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees`
  line `for the limited liability partnership and fifty thousand rupees for designated partners.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (49007)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Inspection of documents kept by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49007&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The incorporation document, names of partners`
  line `and changes, if any, made therein, Statement of Account and Solvency and annual return filed by each`
  line `limited liability partnership with the Registrar shall be available for inspection by any person in such`
  line `manner and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (49008)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Penalty for false statement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49008&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `If in any return, statement or other document required by or for the`
  line `purposes of any of the provisions of this Act, any person makes a statement--`
  line
  line `(a) which is false in any material particular, knowing it to be false; or`
  line
  line `(b) which omits any material fact knowing it to be material,`
  line
  line `he shall, save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to two years, and shall also be liable to fine which may extend to five lakh rupees but`
  line `which shall not be less than one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (49009)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of Registrar to obtain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49009&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) In order to obtain such information as the`
  line `Registrar may consider necessary for the purposes of carrying out the provisions of this Act, the Registrar`
  line `may require any person including any present or former partner or designated partner or employee of a`
  line `limited liability partnership to answer any question or make any declaration or supply any details or`
  line `particulars in writing to him within a reasonable period.`
  line
  line `(2) In case any person referred to in sub-section (1) does not answer such question or make such`
  line `declaration or supply such details or particulars asked for by the Registrar within a reasonable time or`
  line `time given by the Registrar or when the Registrar is not satisfied with the reply or declaration or details or`
  line `particulars provided by such person, the Registrar shall have power to summon that person to appear`
  line `before him or an inspector or any other public officer whom the Registrar may designate, to answer any`
  line `such question or make such declaration or supply such details, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who, without lawful excuse, fails to comply with any summons or requisition of the`
  line `Registrar under this section shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than two thousand rupees`
  line `but which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (49010)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 40
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 16, for section 39 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49010&sectionno=39&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the Regional Director or any other officer not below the rank of Regional`
  line `Director authorised by the Central Government may compound any offence under this Act which is`
  line `punishable with fine only, by collecting from a person reasonably suspected of having committed the`
  line `offence, a sum which may extend to the amount of the maximum fine provided for the offence but shall`
  line `not be lower than the minimum amount provided for the offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to an offence committed by a limited liability`
  line `partnership or its partner or its designated partner within a period of three years from the date on which`
  line `similar offence committed by it or him was compounded under this section.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that any second or subsequent offence`
  line `committed after the expiry of the period of three years from the date on which the offence was previously`
  line `compounded, shall be deemed to be the first offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application for the compounding of an offence shall be made to the Registrar who shall`
  line `forward the same, together with his comments thereon, to the Regional Director or any other officer not`
  line `below the rank of Regional Director authorised by the Central Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any offence is compounded under this section, whether before or after the institution of any`
  line `prosecution, intimation thereof shall be given to the Registrar within a period of seven days from the date`
  line `on which the offence is so compounded.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any offence is compounded before the institution of any prosecution, no prosecution shall`
  line `be instituted in relation to such offence.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the compounding of any offence is made after the institution of any prosecution, such`
  line `compounding shall be brought by the Registrar in writing, to the notice of the court in which prosecution`
  line `is pending and on such notice of the compounding of the offence being given, the offender in relation to`
  line `which the offence is so compounded shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(7) The Regional Director or any other officer not below the rank of Regional Director authorised by`
  line `the Central Government, while dealing with the proposal for compounding of an offence may, by an`
  line `order, direct any partner, designated partner or other employee of the limited liability partnership to file or`
  line `register, or on payment of fee or additional fee as required to be paid under this Act, such return, account`
  line `or other document within such time as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, if any partner or designated partner or other`
  line `employee of the limited liability partnership who fails to comply with any order made by the Regional`
  line `Director or any other officer not below the rank of Regional Director authorised by the Central`
  line `Government, under sub-section (7), the maximum amount of fine for the offence, which was under`
  line `consideration of Regional Director or such authorised officer for compounding under this section shall be`
  line `twice the amount provided in the corresponding section in which punishment for such offence is`
  line provided.
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (49011)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 41
  title `Destruction of old records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49011&sectionno=40&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may destroy any document filed or registered with`
  line `him in physical form or in electronic form in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (49012)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 42
  title `Enforcement of duty to make returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49012&sectionno=41&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any limited liability partnership is in default`
  line `in complying with--`
  line
  line `(a) any provisions of this Act or of any other law which requires the filing in any manner with the`
  line `Registrar of any return, account or other document or the giving of notice to him of any matter; or`
  line
  line `(b) any request of the Registrar to amend or complete and resubmit any document or to submit a`
  line `fresh document,`
  line
  line `and fails to make good the default within fourteen days after the service on the limited liability`
  line `partnership of a notice requiring it to be done, the Tribunal may, on application by the Registrar, make an`
  line `order directing that limited liability partnership or its designated partners or its partners to make good the`
  line `default within such time as specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such order may provide that all the costs of and incidental to the application shall be borne by`
  line `that limited liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall limit the operation of any other provision of this Act or any other law`
  line `imposing penalties in respect of any default referred to in this section on that limited liability partnership.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (49013)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 43
  title `Partner's transferable interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49013&sectionno=42&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The rights of a partner to a share of the profits and losses`
  line `of the limited liability partnership and to receive distributions in accordance with the limited liability`
  line `partnership agreement are transferable either wholly or in part.`
  line
  line `(2) The transfer of any right by any partner pursuant to sub-section (1) does not by itself cause the`
  line `disassociation of the partner or a dissolution and winding up of the limited liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(3) The transfer of right pursuant to this section does not, by itself, entitle the transferee or assignee to`
  line `participate in the management or conduct of the activities of the limited liability partnership, or access`
  line `information concerning the transactions of the limited liability partnership.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (49014)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `Investigation of the affairs of limited liability partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49014&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `appoint one or more competent persons as inspectors to investigate the affairs of a limited liability`
  line `partnership and to report thereon in such manner as it may direct if--`
  line
  line `(a) the Tribunal, either suo motu, or on an application received from not less than one-fifth of the`
  line `total number of partners of limited liability partnership, by order, declares that the affairs of the`
  line `limited liability partnership ought to be investigated; or`
  line
  line `(b) any Court, by order, declares that the affairs of a limited liability partnership ought to be`
  line investigated.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint one or more competent persons as inspectors to investigate`
  line `the affairs of a limited liability partnership and to report on them in such manner as it may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) The appointment of inspectors pursuant to sub-section (2) may be made,--`
  line
  line `(a) if not less than one-fifth of the total number of partners of the limited liability partnership`
  line `make an application along with supporting evidence and security amount as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the limited liability partnership makes an application that the affairs of the limited liability`
  line `partnership ought to be investigated; or`
  line
  line `(c) if, in the opinion of the Central Government, there are circumstances suggesting--`
  line
  line `(i) that the business of the limited liability partnership is being or has been conducted with an`
  line `intent to defraud its creditors, partners or any other person, or otherwise for a fraudulent or`
  line `unlawful purpose, or in a manner oppressive or unfairly prejudicial to some or any of its partners,`
  line `or that the limited liability partnership was formed for any fraudulent or unlawful purpose; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that the affairs of the limited liability partnership are not being conducted in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) that, on receipt of a report of the Registrar or any other investigating or regulatory`
  line `agency, there are sufficient reasons that the affairs of the limited liability partnership ought to be`
  line investigated.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (49015)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 45
  title `Application by partners for investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49015&sectionno=44&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `An application by partners of the limited liability`
  line `partnership under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 43 shall be supported by such evidence as the`
  line `Tribunal may require for the purpose of showing that the applicants have good reason for requiring the`
  line `investigation and the Central Government may, before appointing an inspector, require the applicants to`
  line `give security, of such amount as may be prescribed, for payment of costs of the investigation.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (49016)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 46
  title `Firm, body corporate or association not to be appointed as inspector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49016&sectionno=45&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `No firm, body`
  line `corporate or other association shall be appointed as an inspector.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (49017)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power of inspectors to carry out investigation into affairs of related entities, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49017&sectionno=46&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an`
  line `inspector appointed by the Central Government to investigate the affairs of a limited liability partnership`
  line `thinks it necessary for the purposes of his investigation to investigate also the affairs of an entity which`
  line `has been associated in the past or is presently associated with the limited liability partnership or any`
  line `present or former partner or designated partner of the limited liability partnership, the inspector shall have`
  line `the power to do so and shall report on the affairs of the other entity or partner or designated partner, so far`
  line `as he thinks that the results of his investigation thereof are relevant to the investigation of the affairs of`
  line `the limited liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any entity or partner or designated partner referred to in sub-section (1), the`
  line `inspector shall not exercise his power of investigating into, and reporting on, its or his affairs without`
  line `obtaining the prior approval of the Central Government thereto:`
  line
  line `Provided that before according approval under this sub-section, the Central Government shall give the`
  line `entity or partner or designated partner a reasonable opportunity to show cause why such approval should`
  line `not be accorded.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (49018)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 48
  title `Production of documents and evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49018&sectionno=47&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the designated partner and`
  line `partners of the limited liability partnership--`
  line
  line `(a) to preserve and to produce before an inspector or any person authorised by him in this behalf`
  line `with the previous approval of the Central Government, all books and papers of, or relating to, the`
  line `limited liability partnership or, as the case may be, the other entity, which are in their custody or`
  line `power; and`
  line
  line `(b) otherwise to give to the inspector all assistance in connection with the investigation which`
  line `they are reasonably able to give.`
  line
  line `(2) The inspector may, with the previous approval of the Central Government, require any entity other`
  line `than an entity referred to in sub-section (1) to furnish such information to, or produce such books and`
  line `papers before him or any person authorised by him in this behalf, with the previous approval of that`
  line `Government, as he may consider necessary, if the furnishing of such information or the production of`
  line `such books and papers is relevant or necessary for the purposes of his investigation.`
  line
  line `(3) The inspector may keep in his custody any books and papers produced under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) for thirty days and thereafter shall return the same to the limited liability partnership, other`
  line `entity or individual by whom or on whose behalf the books and papers are produced:`
  line
  line `Provided that the inspector may call for the books and papers if they are needed again:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if certified copies of the books and papers produced under sub-section (2) are`
  line `furnished to the inspector, he shall return those books and papers to the entity or person concerned.`
  line
  line `(4) An inspector may examine on oath--`
  line
  line `(a) any of the persons referred to in sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) with the previous approval of the Central Government, any other person in relation to the`
  line `affairs of the limited liability partnership or any other entity, as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(c) may administer an oath accordingly and for that purpose may require any of those persons to`
  line `appear before him personally.`
  line
  line `(5) If any person fails without reasonable cause or refuses--`
  line
  line `(a) to produce before an inspector or any person authorised by him in this behalf with the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government any book or paper which it is his duty under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) to produce; or`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish any information which is his duty under sub-section (2) to furnish; or`
  line
  line `(c) to appear before the inspector personally when required to do so under sub-section (4) or to`
  line `answer any question which is put to him by the inspector in pursuance of that sub-section; or`
  line
  line `(d) to sign the notes of any examination,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than two thousand rupees but which may extend`
  line `to twenty-five thousand rupees and with a further fine which shall not be less than fifty rupees but which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees for every day after the first day after which the default continues.`
  line
  line `(6) The notes of any examination under sub-section (4) shall be taken down in writing and signed by`
  line `the person whose examination was made on oath and a copy of such notes shall be given to the person so`
  line `examined on oath and thereafter be used as an evidence by the inspector.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (49019)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 49
  title `Seizure of documents by inspector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49019&sectionno=48&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in the course of investigation, the inspector has`
  line `reasonable ground to believe that the books and papers of, or relating to, the limited liability partnership`
  line `or other entity or partner or designated partner of such limited liability partnership may be destroyed,`
  line `mutilated, altered, falsified or secreted, the inspector may make an application to the Judicial Magistrate`
  line `of the first class, or, as the case may be, the Metropolitan Magistrate, having jurisdiction, for an order for`
  line `the seizure of such books and papers.`
  line
  line `(2) After considering the application and hearing the inspector, if necessary, the Magistrate may, by`
  line `order, authorise the inspector--`
  line
  line `(a) to enter, with such assistance, as may be required, the place or places where such books and`
  line `papers are kept;`
  line
  line `(b) to search that place or those places in the manner specified in the order; and`
  line
  line `(c) to seize books and papers which the inspector considers it necessary for the purposes of his`
  line investigation.
  line
  line `(3) The inspector shall keep in his custody the books and papers seized under this section for such`
  line `period not later than the conclusion of the investigation as he considers necessary and thereafter shall`
  line `return the same to the concerned entity or person from whose custody or power they were seized and`
  line `inform the Magistrate of such return:`
  line
  line `Provided that the books and papers shall not be kept seized for a continuous period of more than six`
  line `months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the inspector may, before returning such books and papers as aforesaid, place`
  line `identification marks on them or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) Save as otherwise provided in this section, every search or seizure made under this section shall`
  line `be carried out in accordance with the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)`
  line `relating to searches or seizures made under that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (49020)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 50
  title `Inspector's report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49020&sectionno=49&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Inspector may, and if so directed by the Central Government, shall`
  line `make interim reports to that Government, and on the conclusion of the investigation, shall make a final`
  line `report to the Central Government and any such report shall be written or printed, as the Central`
  line `Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government--`
  line
  line `(a) shall forward a copy of any report (other than an interim report) made by the inspectors to the`
  line `limited liability partnership at its registered office, and also to any other entity or person dealt with or`
  line `related to the report; and`
  line
  line `(b) may, if it thinks fit, furnish a copy thereof, on request and on payment of the prescribed fee, to`
  line `any person or entity related to or affected by the report.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (49021)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 51
  title Prosecution.
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49021&sectionno=50&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `If, from the report under section 49, it appears to the Central Government that any`
  line `person in relation to the limited liability partnership or in relation to any other entity whose affairs have`
  line `been investigated, has been guilty of any offence for which he is liable, the Central Government may`
  line `prosecute such person for the offence; and it shall be the duty of all partners, designated partners and`
  line `other employees and agents of the limited liability partnership or other entity, as the case may be, to give`
  line `the Central Government all assistance in connection with the prosecution which they are reasonably able`
  line `to give.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (49022)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 52
  title `Application for winding up of limited liability partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49022&sectionno=51&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `If any such limited liability`
  line `partnership is liable to be wound up under this Act or any other law for the time being in force, and it`
  line `appears to the Central Government from any such report under section 49 that it is expedient to do so by`
  line `reason of any such circumstances as are referred to in sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 43, the Central Government may, unless the limited liability partnership is`
  line `already being wound up by the Tribunal, cause to be presented to the Tribunal by any person authorised`
  line `by the Central Government in this behalf, a petition for the winding up of the limited liability partnership`
  line `on the ground that it is just and equitable that it should be wound up.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (49023)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 53
  title `Proceedings for recovery of damages or property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49023&sectionno=52&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `If, from any report under section 49, it`
  line `appears to the Central Government that proceedings ought, in the public interest, to be brought by the`
  line `limited liability partnership or any entity whose affairs have been investigated,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the recovery of damages in respect of any fraud, misfeasance or other misconduct in`
  line `connection with the promotion or formation, or the management of the affairs, of such limited`
  line `liability partnership or such other entity; or`
  line
  line `(b) for the recovery of any property of such limited liability partnership or such other entity,`
  line `which has been misapplied or wrongfully retained,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may itself bring proceedings for that purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (49024)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 54
  title `Expenses of investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49024&sectionno=53&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The expenses of, and incidental to, an investigation by an`
  line `inspector appointed by the Central Government under this Act shall be defrayed in the first instance by`
  line `the Central Government; but the following persons shall, to the extent mentioned below, be liable to`
  line `reimburse the Central Government in respect of such expenses, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) any person who is convicted on a prosecution, or who is ordered to pay damages or restore`
  line `any property in proceedings brought by virtue of section 52, may, in the same proceedings, be ordered`
  line `to pay the said expenses to such extent as may be specified by the court convicting such person, or`
  line `ordering him to pay such damages or restore such property, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) any entity in whose name proceedings are brought as aforesaid shall be liable, to the extent of`
  line `the amount or value of any sums or property recovered by it as a result of the proceedings; and`
  line
  line `(c) unless, as a result of the investigation, a prosecution is instituted in pursuance of section 50,--`
  line
  line `(i) any entity, a partner or designated partner or any other person dealt with by the report of`
  line `the inspector shall be liable to reimburse the Central Government in respect of the whole of the`
  line `expenses, unless and except in so far as, the Central Government otherwise directs; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the applicants for the investigation, where the inspector was appointed in pursuance of the`
  line `provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 43, shall be liable to such extent, if any, as`
  line `the Central Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount for which a limited liability partnership or other entity is liable by virtue of clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (1) shall be a first charge on the sums or property mentioned in that clause.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of expenses in respect of which any limited liability partnership, other entity, a`
  line `partner or designated partner or any other person is liable under sub-clause (i) of clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) to reimburse the Central Government shall be recoverable as arrears of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section, any costs or expenses incurred by the Central Government or in`
  line `connection with the proceedings brought by virtue of section 52 shall be treated as expenses of the`
  line `investigation giving rise to the proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (49025)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 55
  title `Inspector's report to be evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49025&sectionno=54&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `A copy of any report of any inspector or inspectors`
  line `appointed under the provisions of this Act, authenticated in such manner, if any, as may be prescribed,`
  line `shall be admissible in any legal proceeding as evidence in relation to any matter contained in the report.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (49026)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 56
  title `Conversion from firm into limited liability partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49026&sectionno=55&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `A firm may convert into a limited`
  line `liability partnership in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (49027)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 57
  title `Conversion from private company into limited liability partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49027&sectionno=56&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `A private company`
  line `may convert into a limited liability partnership in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and the`
  line `Third Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (49028)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 58
  title `Conversion from unlisted public company into limited liability partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49028&sectionno=57&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `An unlisted`
  line `public company may convert into a limited liability partnership in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter and the Fourth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (49029)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 59
  title `Registration and effect of conversion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 2, for “the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)” (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49029&sectionno=58&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar, on satisfying that a firm, private`
  line `company or an unlisted public company, as the case may be, has complied with the provisions of the`
  line `Second Schedule, the Third Schedule or the Fourth Schedule, as the case may be, shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, register the documents submitted under such`
  line `Schedule and issue a certificate of registration in such form as the Registrar may determine stating that`
  line `the limited liability partnership is, on and from the date specified in the certificate, registered under this`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the limited liability partnership shall, within fifteen days of the date of registration,`
  line `inform the concerned Registrar of Firms or Registrar of Companies, as the case may be, with which it was`
  line `registered under the provisions of the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932) or ^1[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] as the case may be, about the conversion and of the particulars of the limited liability`
  line `partnership in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon such conversion, the partners of the firm, the shareholders of private company or unlisted`
  line `public company, as the case may be, the limited liability partnership to which such firm or such company`
  line `has converted, and the partners of the limited liability partnership shall be bound by the provisions of the`
  line `Second Schedule, the Third Schedule or the Fourth Schedule, as the case may be, applicable to them.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon such conversion, on and from the date of certificate of registration, the effects of the`
  line `conversion shall be such as specified in the Second Schedule, the Third Schedule or the Fourth Schedule,`
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, on and from the`
  line `date of registration specified in the certificate of registration issued under the Second Schedule, the Third`
  line `Schedule or the Fourth Schedule, as the case may be,--`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be a limited liability partnership by the name specified in the certificate of`
  line `registration registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) all tangible (movable or immovable) and intangible property vested in the firm or the`
  line `company, as the case may be, all assets, interests, rights, privileges, liabilities, obligations relating to`
  line `the firm or the company, as the case may be, and the whole of the undertaking of the firm or the`
  line `company, as the case may be, shall be transferred to and shall vest in the limited liability partnership`
  line `without further assurance, act or deed; and`
  line
  line `(c) the firm or the company, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be dissolved and removed`
  line `from the records of the Registrar of Firms or Registrar of Companies, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (49030)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 60
  title `Foreign limited liability partnerships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 2, for “the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)” (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49030&sectionno=59&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make rules for`
  line `provisions in relation to establishment of place of business by foreign limited liability partnerships within`
  line `India and carrying on their business therein by applying or incorporating, with such modifications, as`
  line `appear appropriate, the provisions of ^1[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] or such regulatory mechanism`
  line `with such composition as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (49031)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 61
  title `Compromise, or arrangement of limited liability partnerships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 17, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).br`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49031&sectionno=60&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a compromise or`
  line `arrangement is proposed--`
  line
  line `(a) between a limited liability partnership and its creditors; or`
  line
  line `(b) between a limited liability partnership and its partners,`
  line
  line `the Tribunal may, on the application of the limited liability partnership or of any creditor or partner of the`
  line `limited liability partnership, or, in the case of a limited liability partnership which is being wound up, of`
  line `the liquidator, order a meeting of the creditors or of the partners, as the case may be, to be called, held and`
  line `conducted in such manner as may be prescribed or as the Tribunal directs.`
  line
  line `(2) If a majority representing three-fourths in value of the creditors, or partners, as the case may be, at`
  line `the meeting, agree to any compromise or arrangement, the compromise or arrangement shall, if`
  line `sanctioned by the Tribunal, by order be binding on all the creditors or all the partners, as the case may be,`
  line `and also on the limited liability partnership, or in the case of a limited liability partnership which is being`
  line `wound up, on the liquidator and contributories of the limited liability partnership:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order sanctioning any compromise or arrangement shall be made by the Tribunal`
  line `unless the Tribunal is satisfied that the limited liability partnership or any other person by whom an`
  line `application has been made under sub-section (1) has disclosed to the Tribunal, by affidavit or otherwise,`
  line `all material facts relating to the limited liability partnership, including the latest financial position of the`
  line `limited liability partnership and the pendency of any investigation proceedings in relation to the limited`
  line `liability partnership.`
  line
  line `(3) An order made by the Tribunal under sub-section (2) shall be filed by the limited liability`
  line `partnership with the Registrar within thirty days after making such an order and shall have effect only`
  line `after it is so filed.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) If default is made in complying with the provisions of sub-section (3), the limited liability`
  line `partnership and its every designated partner shall be liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees, and in case`
  line `of continuing default, with a further penalty of one hundred rupees for each day after the first during`
  line `which such default continues, subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees for limited liability partnership`
  line `and fifty thousand rupees for every designated partner.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal may, at any time after an application has been made to it under this section, stay the`
  line `commencement or continuation of any suit or proceeding against the limited liability partnership on such`
  line `terms as the Tribunal thinks fit, until the application is finally disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (49032)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power of Tribunal to enforce compromise or arrangement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49032&sectionno=61&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Tribunal makes an`
  line `order under section 60 sanctioning a compromise or an arrangement in respect of a limited liability`
  line `partnership, it--`
  line
  line `(a) shall have power to supervise the carrying out of the compromise or an arrangement; and`
  line
  line `(b) may, at the time of making such order or at any time thereafter, give such directions in regard`
  line `to any matter or make such modifications in the compromise or arrangement as it may consider`
  line `necessary for the proper working of the compromise or arrangement.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Tribunal aforesaid is satisfied that a compromise or an arrangement sanctioned under`
  line `section 60 cannot be worked satisfactorily with or without modifications, it may, either on its own motion`
  line `or on the application of any person interested in the affairs of the limited liability partnership, make an`
  line `order for winding up the limited liability partnership, and such an order shall be deemed to be an order`
  line `made under section 64 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (49033)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 63
  title `Provisions for facilitating reconstruction or amalgamation of limited liability partnerships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 18, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49033&sectionno=62&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an application is made to the Tribunal under section 60 for sanctioning of a`
  line `compromise or arrangement proposed between a limited liability partnership and any such persons as are`
  line `mentioned in that section, and it is shown to the Tribunal that--`
  line
  line `(a) compromise or arrangement has been proposed for the purposes of, or in connection with, a`
  line `scheme for the reconstruction of any limited liability partnership or limited liability partnerships, or`
  line `the amalgamation of any two or more limited liability partnerships; and`
  line
  line `(b) under the scheme the whole or any part of the undertaking, property or liabilities of any`
  line `limited liability partnership concerned in the scheme (in this section referred to as a transferor`
  line `limited liability partnership) is to be transferred to another limited liability partnership (in this`
  line `section referred to as the transferee limited liability partnership), the Tribunal may, either by the`
  line `order sanctioning the compromise or arrangement or by a subsequent order, make provisions for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the transfer to the transferee limited liability partnership of the whole or any part of the`
  line `undertaking, property or liabilities of any transferor limited liability partnership;`
  line
  line `(ii) the continuation by or against the transferee limited liability partnership of any legal`
  line `proceedings pending by or against any transferor limited liability partnership;`
  line
  line `(iii) the dissolution, without winding up, of any transferor limited liability partnership;`
  line
  line `(iv) the provision to be made for any person who, within such time and in such manner as the`
  line `Tribunal directs, dissent from the compromise or arrangement; and`
  line
  line `(v) such incidental, consequential and supplemental matters as are necessary to secure that the`
  line `reconstruction or amalgamation shall be fully and effectively carried out:`
  line
  line `Provided that no compromise or arrangement proposed for the purposes of, or in connection`
  line `with, a scheme for the amalgamation of a limited liability partnership, which is being wound up,`
  line `with any other limited liability partnership or limited liability partnerships, shall be sanctioned by`
  line `the Tribunal unless the Tribunal has received a report from the Registrar that the affairs of the`
  line `limited liability partnership have not been conducted in a manner prejudicial to the interests of its`
  line `partners or to public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no order for the dissolution of any transferor limited liability partnership`
  line `under clause (iii) shall be made by the Tribunal unless the Official Liquidator has, on scrutiny of`
  line `the books and papers of the limited liability partnership, made a report to the Tribunal that the`
  line `affairs of the limited liability partnership have not been conducted in a manner prejudicial to the`
  line `interests of its partners or to public interest.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order under this section provides for the transfer of any property or liabilities, then, by`
  line `virtue of the order, that property shall be transferred to and vest in, and those liabilities shall be`
  line `transferred to and become the liabilities of, the transferee limited liability partnership; and in the case of`
  line `any property, if the order so directs, freed from any charge which is, by virtue of the compromise or`
  line `arrangement, to cease to have effect.`
  line
  line `(3) Within thirty days after the making of an order under this section, every limited liability`
  line `partnership in relation to which the order is made shall cause a certified copy thereof to be filed with the`
  line `Registrar for registration.`
  line
  line `^1[(4) If default is made in complying with the provisions of sub-section (3), the limited liability`
  line `partnership and its every designated partner shall be liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees, and in case`
  line `of the continuing default, with a further penalty of one hundred rupees for each day, after the first during`
  line `which such default continues, subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees for limited liability partnership`
  line `and fifty thousand rupees for every designated partner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(i) “property” includes property, rights and powers of every description and “liabilities” includes`
  line `duties of every description;`
  line
  line `(ii) a “limited liability partnership” shall not be amalgamated with a company.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section property includes property, rights and powers of every description;`
  line `and liabilities includes duties of every description.`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (49034)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 64
  title `Winding up and dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49034&sectionno=63&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The winding up of a limited liability partnership may be either`
  line `voluntary or by the Tribunal and limited liability partnership, so wound up may be dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (49035)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 65
  title `Circumstances in which limited liability partnership may be wound up by Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (c) omitted by Act 31 of 2016, s. 254 and the Tenth Schedule (w.e.f. 15-11-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49035&sectionno=64&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line A
  line `limited liability partnership may be wound up by the Tribunal,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the limited liability partnership decides that limited liability partnership be wound up by the`
  line Tribunal;
  line
  line `(b) if, for a period of more than six months, the number of partners of the limited liability`
  line `partnership is reduced below two;`
  line
  line *****
  line ;
  line
  line `(d) if the limited liability partnership has acted against the interests of the sovereignty and`
  line `integrity of India, the security of the State or public order;`
  line
  line `(e) if the limited liability partnership has made a default in filing with the Registrar the Statement`
  line `of Account and Solvency or annual return for any five consecutive financial years; or`
  line
  line `(f) if the Tribunal is of the opinion that it is just and equitable that the limited liability partnership`
  line `be wound up.`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (49036)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 66
  title `Rules for winding up and dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49036&sectionno=65&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make rules for the`
  line `provisions in relation to winding up and dissolution of limited liability partnerships.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (49037)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 67
  title `Business transactions of partner with limited liability partnership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49037&sectionno=66&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `A partner may lend`
  line `money to and transact other business with the limited liability partnership and has the same rights and`
  line `obligations with respect to the loan or other transactions as a person who is not a partner.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (49038)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 68
  title `Application of the provisions of the Companies Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49038&sectionno=67&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification* in the Official Gazette, direct that any of the provisions of ^1[the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013)] specified in the notification--`
  line
  line `(a) shall apply to any limited liability partnership; or`
  line
  line `(b) shall apply to any limited liability partnership with such exception, modification and`
  line `adaptation, as may be specified, in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification proposed to be issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid in draft`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `disapproving the issue of the notification or both Houses agree in making any modification in the`
  line `notification, the notification shall not be issued or, as the case may be, shall be issued only in such`
  line `modified form as may be agreed upon by both the Houses.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line `* Vide Notification No. G.S.R. 59(E), dated 30th January, 2020, Central Government hereby directs that the provisions of section 460 of the Company Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), shall apply to a limited partnership from 30th January, 2020.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 2, for the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_67_a:
  sectionId (63906)
  sectionNo 67A
  orderNo 69
  title `Establishment of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 19, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=63906&sectionno=67A&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_67_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Central Government may, for the purpose of`
  line `providing speedy trial of offences under this Act, by notification, establish or designate as many Special`
  line `Courts as may be necessary for such area or areas, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The Special Court shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a single Judge holding office as Sessions Judge or Additional Sessions Judge, in case of`
  line `offences punishable under this Act with imprisonment of three years or more; and`
  line
  line `(b) a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class, in the case of other`
  line offences,
  line `who shall be appointed by the Central Government with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High`
  line `Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that until Special Courts are designated or established under sub-section (1), the Courts`
  line `designated as Special Courts in terms of section 435 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) shall be`
  line `deemed to be Special Courts for the purpose of trial of offences punishable under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), any offence committed under this Act, which is triable by a Special Court shall, until a`
  line `Special Court is established under this Act or the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), be tried by a Court`
  line `of Sessions or the Court of Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class, as the case`
  line `may be, exercising jurisdiction over the area.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_b:
  sectionId (63907)
  sectionNo 67B
  orderNo 70
  title `Procedure and powers of Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 19, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=63907&sectionno=67B&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_67_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all offences specified under sub-section (1) of section 67A`
  line `shall be triable only by the Special Court established or designated for the area in which the registered`
  line `office of the limited liability partnership is situated in relation to which the offence is committed or where`
  line `there are more than one Special Courts for such area, by such one of them as may be specified in this`
  line `behalf by the High Court concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) While trying an offence under this Act, a Special Court may also try an offence other than an`
  line `offence under this Act with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974) be charged at the same trial.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the`
  line `Special Court may, if it thinks fit, try in a summary way any offence under this Act which is punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term not exceeding three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any conviction in a summary trial, no sentence of imprisonment for a term`
  line `exceeding one year shall be passed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, when at the commencement of or in the course of a summary trial, it appears to`
  line `the Special Court that the nature of the case is such that the sentence of imprisonment for a term`
  line `exceeding one year may have to be passed or that it is, for any other reason, undesirable to try the case`
  line `summarily, the Special Court shall, after hearing the parties, record an order to that effect and thereafter`
  line `recall any witnesses who may have been examined and proceed to hear or re-hear the case in accordance`
  line `with the procedure for the regular trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_c:
  sectionId (63908)
  sectionNo 67C
  orderNo 71
  title `Appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 19, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=63908&sectionno=67C&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_67_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[The High Court may exercise, so far as may be applicable, all the`
  line `powers conferred by Chapters XXIX and XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) on a`
  line `High Court, as if a Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court were a Court`
  line `of Sessions trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (49039)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 72
  title `Electronic filing of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49039&sectionno=68&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any document required to be filed, recorded or registered`
  line `under this Act may be filed, recorded or registered in such manner and subject to such conditions as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of or an extract from any document electronically filed with or submitted to the Registrar`
  line `which is supplied or issued by the Registrar and certified through affixing digital signature as per the`
  line `Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000) to be a true copy of or extract from such document shall,`
  line `in any proceedings, be admissible in evidence as of equal validity with the original document.`
  line
  line `(3) Any information supplied by the Registrar that is certified by the Registrar through affixing`
  line `digital signature to be a true extract from any document filed with or submitted to the Registrar shall, in`
  line `any proceedings, be admissible in evidence and be presumed, unless evidence to the contrary is adduced,`
  line `to be a true extract from such document.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68_a:
  sectionId (63909)
  sectionNo 68A
  orderNo 73
  title `Registration offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=63909&sectionno=68A&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_68_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) For the purpose of exercising such powers and discharging such`
  line `functions as are conferred on the Central Government by or under this Act or under rules made thereunder`
  line `and for the purpose of registration of limited liability partnerships under this Act, the Central Government`
  line `shall, by notification, establish such number of registration offices at such places as it thinks fit,`
  line `specifying their jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such Registrars, Additional Registrars, Joint Registrars,`
  line `Deputy Registrars and Assistant Registrars as it considers necessary, for the registration of limited`
  line `liability partnerships and discharge of various functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The powers and duties of the Registrars referred to in sub-section (2) and the terms and conditions`
  line `of their service shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may direct the Registrar to prepare a seal or seals for the authentication`
  line `of documents required for, or connected with the registration of limited liability partnerships.]`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (49040)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 74
  title `Payment of additional fee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for section 69 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49040&sectionno=69&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `^1[Any document or return required to be registered or filed under`
  line `this Act with Registrar, if, is not registered or filed in time provided therein, may be registered or filed`
  line `after that time, on payment of such additional fee as may be prescribed in addition to any fee as is payable`
  line `for filing of such document or return:`
  line
  line `Provided that such document or return shall be filed after the due date of filing, without prejudice to`
  line `any other action or liability under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a different fee or additional fee may be prescribed for different classes of limited`
  line `liability partnerships or for different documents or returns required to be filed under this Act or rules`
  line `made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (49041)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 75
  title `Enhanced punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49041&sectionno=70&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `In case a limited liability partnership or any partner or designated`
  line `partner of such limited liability partnership commits any offence, the limited liability partnership or any`
  line `partner or designated partner shall, for the second or subsequent offence, be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment as provided, but in case of offences for which fine is prescribed either along with or`
  line `exclusive of imprisonment, with fine which shall be twice the amount of fine for such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (49042)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 76
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49042&sectionno=71&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (49043)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 77
  title `Jurisdiction of Tribunal and Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 22, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49043&sectionno=72&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall exercise such powers`
  line `and perform such functions as are, or may be, conferred on it by or under this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Any person aggrieved by an order of Tribunal may prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal shall lie to the Appellate Tribunal from an order made by the Tribunal with`
  line `the consent of parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal preferred under sub-section (2) shall be filed within a period of sixty days from the`
  line `date on which the copy of the order of the Tribunal is made available to the person aggrieved and shall be`
  line `in such form, and accompanied by such fees, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `sixty days, but within a further period of not exceeding sixty days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was`
  line `prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal within the period so specified.`
  line
  line `(4) On the receipt of an appeal under sub-section (2), the Appellate Tribunal shall, after giving the`
  line `parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming,`
  line `modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the Tribunal and the parties`
  line `to the appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (49044)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 78
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49044&sectionno=73&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `[Penalty on non-compliance of any order passed by Tribunal]. Omitted by the Limited Liability`
  line `Partnership (Amendment) Act, 2021 (31 of 2021), s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (49045)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 79
  title `General penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for section 74 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49045&sectionno=74&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `^1[ If a limited liability partnership or any partner or any designated partner`
  line `or any other person contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, or any`
  line `condition, limitation or restriction subject to which any approval, sanction, consent, confirmation,`
  line `recognition, direction or exemption in relation to any matter has been accorded, given or granted, and for`
  line `which no penalty or punishment is provided elsewhere in this Act, the limited liability partnership or any`
  line `partner or any designated partner or any other person, who is in the default, shall be liable to a penalty of`
  line `five thousand rupees and in case of a continuing contravention with a further penalty of one hundred`
  line `rupees for each day after the first during which such contravention continues, subject to a maximum of`
  line `one lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (49046)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 80
  title `Power of Registrar to strike defunct limited liability partnership off register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49046&sectionno=75&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Where the`
  line `Registrar has reasonable cause to believe that a limited liability partnership is not carrying on business or`
  line `its operation, in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the name of limited liability partnership may`
  line `be struck off the register of limited liability partnerships in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar shall, before striking off the name of any limited liability partnership`
  line `under this section, give such limited liability partnership a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (49047)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 81
  title `Offences to limited liability partnerships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49047&sectionno=76&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `Where an offence under this Act committed by a`
  line `limited liability partnership is proved--`
  line
  line `(a) to have been committed with the consent or connivance of a partner or partners or designated`
  line `partner or designated partners of the limited liability partnership; or`
  line
  line `(b) to be attributable to any neglect on the part of the partner or partners or designated partner or`
  line `designated partners of that limited liability partnership,`
  line
  line `the partner or partners or designated partner or designated partners of the limited liability partnership, as`
  line `the case may be, as well as that limited liability partnership shall be guilty of the offence and shall be`
  line `liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76_a:
  sectionId (63910)
  sectionNo 76A
  orderNo 82
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins by Act 31 of 2021, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=63910&sectionno=76A&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_76_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) For the purposes of adjudging penalties under this Act, the`
  line `Central Government may, by an order published in the Official Gazette, appoint as many officers of the`
  line `Central Government, not below the rank of Registrar, as adjudicating officers in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, while appointing adjudicating officers, specify their jurisdiction in`
  line `the order under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The adjudicating officer may, by an order--`
  line
  line `(a) impose the penalty on the limited liability partnership or its partners or designated partners or`
  line `any other person, as the case may be, stating therein any non-compliance or default under the relevant`
  line `provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case default relates to non-compliance of sub-section (3) of section 34 or subsection (1) of section 35 and such default has been rectified either prior to or within thirty days of the`
  line `issue of the notice by the adjudicating officer, no penalty shall be imposed in this regard and`
  line `proceedings under this section in respect of such default shall be deemed to be concluded:`
  line
  line `Provided further that notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if penalty is payable for`
  line `non-compliance of any of the provisions of this Act by a small limited liability partnership or a startup limited liability partnership or by its partner or designated partner or any other person in respect of`
  line `such limited liability partnership, then such limited liability partnership or its partner or designated`
  line `partner or any other person, shall be liable to a penalty which shall be one-half of the penalty`
  line `specified in such provisions subject to a maximum of one lakh rupees for limited liability partnership`
  line `and fifty thousand rupees for every partner or designated partner or any other person, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this proviso, the expression “start-up limited liability`
  line `partnership” means a limited liability partnership incorporated under this Act and recognised as such`
  line `in accordance with the notifications issued by the Central Government from time to time.`
  line
  line `(b) direct such limited liability partnership or its partner or designated partner or any other person,`
  line `as the case may be, to rectify the default, wherever he considers fit for reasons to be recorded in`
  line writing.
  line
  line `(4) The adjudicating officer shall, before imposing any penalty, give an opportunity of being heard to`
  line `such limited liability partnership or its partner or designated partner or any other person, who is in default.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person aggrieved by an order made by the adjudicating officer under sub-section (3) may`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Regional Director having jurisdiction in the matter.`
  line
  line `(6) Every appeal made under sub-section (5) shall be filed within a period of sixty days from the date`
  line `on which the copy of the order made by the adjudicating officer is received by the aggrieved person and`
  line `shall be in such form, manner and accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Regional Director may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the period`
  line `of filing an appeal, under this sub-section, by not more than thirty days.`
  line
  line `(7) The Regional Director may, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the parties to the appeal,`
  line `pass such order as he thinks fit, confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(8) Where a limited liability partnership fails to comply with the order made under sub-section (3) or`
  line `sub-section (7), as the case may be, within a period of ninety days from the date of receipt of the copy of`
  line `the order, such limited liability partnership shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees, but may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(9) Where a partner or designated partner of a limited liability partnership or any other person who is`
  line `in default fails to comply with an order made under sub-section (3) or sub-section (7), as the case may be,`
  line `within a period of ninety days from the date of receipt of the copy of the order, such partner or designated`
  line `partner or any other person shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to six months or`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than twenty-five thousand rupees but may extend to one lakh rupees, or`
  line `with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (49048)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 83
  title `Jurisdiction of Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 31of 2021, s. 26, for section 77 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49048&sectionno=77&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `^1[Subject to the provisions contained in section 67A and section 67B,`
  line `on and from the date of establishment or designation of Special Courts under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) the Special Court referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 67A shall have`
  line `jurisdiction and power to impose punishment under section 30 of the Act; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the criminal cases against the limited liability partnership or its partners or designated partners`
  line `or any other person in default filed under this Act and pending before the court of Judicial Magistrate`
  line `of the first class or Metropolitan Magistrate, as the case may be, shall be transferred to the Special`
  line `Court referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 67A.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_a:
  sectionId (63911)
  sectionNo 77A
  orderNo 84
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_a_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 31of 2021, s. 26, for section 77 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=63911&sectionno=77A&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_77_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[No court, other than the Special Courts referred to in section 67A,`
  line `shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this Act or the rules made thereunder save on a`
  line `complaint in writing made by the Registrar or by any officer not below the rank of Registrar duly`
  line `authorised by the Central Government for this purpose.]`
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (49049)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to alter Schedules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49049&sectionno=78&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, alter any of the provisions contained in any of the Schedules to this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any alteration notified under sub-section (1) shall have effect as if enacted in the Act and shall`
  line `come into force on the date of the notification, unless the notification otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `(3) Every alteration made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the alteration, or both Houses agree that the alteration should not be`
  line `made, the alteration shall, thereafter, have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done in pursuance of that alteration.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (49050)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49050&sectionno=79&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the contribution of such higher amount under sub-clauses (i) and (ii) of clause (ta) of`
  line `section 2;`
  line
  line `(aa) the terms and conditions to be fulfilled by class or classes of limited liability partnerships`
  line `under long line to clause (ta) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(ab) the form and manner of prior consent to be given by designated partner under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 7;]`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner of particulars of every individual agreeing to act as designated partner of`
  line `limited liability partnership under sub-section (4) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions and requirements relating to the eligibility of an individual to become a`
  line `designated partner under sub-section (5) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of filing the incorporation document and payment of fees payable thereof under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of statement to be filed under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) the form of incorporation document under clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) the information to be contained in the incorporation document concerning the proposed`
  line `limited liability partnership under clause (g) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of serving the documents on a limited liability partnership or a partner or a`
  line `designated partner and the form and manner in which any other address may be declared by the`
  line `limited liability partnership under sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(i) the form and manner of notice to the Registrar and the conditions in respect of change of`
  line `registered office under sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and manner of application and amount of fee payable to the Registrar under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which names will be reserved by the Registrar under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `^1[(ka) the manner of allotting a new name to the limited liability partnership under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 17;]`
  line
  line `(l) the manner in which an application may be made by an entity under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 18;`
  line
  line `(m) the form and manner of notice of change of name of limited liability partnership and the`
  line `amount of fee payable under section 19;`
  line
  line `(n) the form and manner of the limited liability partnership agreement and the changes made`
  line `therein and the amount of fee payable under sub-section (2) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(o) the form of notice, the amount of fee payable and the manner of authentication of the`
  line `statement under clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner of accounting and disclosure of monetary value of contribution of a partner under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(q) the books of account and the period of their maintenance under sub-section (1) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(r) the form of Statement of Account and Solvency under sub-section (2) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(s) the form, manner, fee and time of filing of Statement of Account and Solvency under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 34;`
  line
  line `(t) the audit of accounts of a limited liability partnership under sub-section (4) of section 34;`
  line
  line `^2[(ta) the standards of accounting and auditing under section 34A;]`
  line
  line `(u) the form and manner of annual return and fee payable under sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(v) the manner and amount of fee payable for inspection of incorporation document, names of`
  line `partners and changes made therein, Statement of Account and Solvency and annual return under`
  line `section 36;`
  line
  line `(w) the destruction of documents by Registrar in any form under section 40;`
  line
  line `(x) the amount required as security under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 43;`
  line
  line `(y) the amount of security to be given under section 44;`
  line
  line `(z) the fee payable for furnishing a copy under clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 49;`
  line
  line `(za) the manner of authentication of report of inspector under section 54;`
  line
  line `(zb) the form and manner of particulars about conversion under the proviso to sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 58;`
  line
  line `(zc) in relation to establishment of place of business and carrying on business in India by foreign`
  line `limited liability partnerships and regulatory mechanism and composition under section 59;`
  line
  line `(zd) the manner of calling, holding and conducting meeting under sub-section (1) of section 60;`
  line
  line `(ze) in relation to winding up and dissolution of limited liability partnerships under section 65;`
  line
  line `(zf) the manner and conditions for filing document electronically under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 68;`
  line
  line `^1[(zfa) the powers and duties to be discharged by the Registrars and the terms and conditions of`
  line `their service under sub-section (3) of section 68A;;`
  line
  line `(zfb) the payment of additional fee for filing of document or return and the payment of different`
  line `fee or additional fee under section 69;;`
  line
  line `(zfc) the form and fee for filing of appeal under sub-section (3) of section 72;];`
  line
  line `(zg) the manner for striking off the names of limited liability partnerships from the register under`
  line `section 75;`
  line
  line `^1[(zga) the manner of appointing adjudicating officers for adjudging penalty under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 76A;`
  line
  line `(zgb) the form, manner and fee for filing an appeal against the order made by the adjudicating`
  line `officer under sub-section (6) of section 76A;]`
  line
  line `(zh) the form and manner of statement containing particulars and amount of fee payable under`
  line `sub-paragraph (a) of paragraph 4 of the Second Schedule;`
  line
  line `(zi) the form and manner of particulars about conversion under the proviso to paragraph 5 of the`
  line `Second Schedule;`
  line
  line `(zj) the form and manner of the statement and the amount of fee payable under sub-paragraph (a)`
  line `of paragraph 3 of the Third Schedule;`
  line
  line `(zk) the form and manner of particulars about conversion under the proviso to paragraph 4 of the`
  line `Third Schedule;`
  line
  line `(zl) the form and manner of the statement and amount of fee payable under sub-paragraph (a) of`
  line `paragraph 4 of the Fourth Schedule; ^3***`
  line
  line `(zm) the form and manner of particulars about conversion under the proviso to paragraph 5 of the`
  line `Fourth Schedule.`
  line
  line `^2[(zn) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made by rules.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act by the Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall,`
  line `thereafter, have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  line `3. The word and omitted by s. 27, ibid., (w.e.f 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (49051)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 87
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2021, s. 28(w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49051&sectionno=80&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years`
  line `from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if any difficulty arises in giving effect`
  line `to the provisions of this Act as amended by the Limited Liability Partnership (Amendment) Act, 2021, the`
  line `Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of three years`
  line `from the date of commencement of the Limited Liability Partnership (Amendment) Act, 2021.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (49052)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 88
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904&sectionId=49052&sectionno=81&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_22_29_00007_200906_1517807325904
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `[Transitional provisions.] Omitted by the Limited Liability Partnership (Amendment) Act, 2021 (31 of`
  line `2021), s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
